  "answer": "**Manusmṛti Chapter 7 in the Falsafa corpus contains 86 verses (numbered Mn_7.1 through Mn_7.86), which discuss the duties and conduct of kings, including their divine origin, the role of punishment (*daṇḍa*), counsel with ministers, forts, vices to avoid, and gifts to Brahmins.[^1]**\n\n**Verse 7.99 (or verses thereabouts, e.g., 87–99) is not present in this version of the text, as the chapter ends at verse 86. The corpus does not cover it, so its specific prescription cannot be provided from available sources.**\n\n[^1]: Manu, *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 7, [translation](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/07/translation/).",
